# 2026-06-02 — Andrew "look at safari": GitHub Actions deploy has
# been failing for ~5 hours because `npm ci` rejected the peer-dep
# conflict introduced when @capacitor-firebase/messaging was added
# (it pins firebase v12 as peer dep; this project uses firebase v10
# for the web SDK). Locally I worked around it with --legacy-peer-deps
# on every install, but CI's `npm ci` doesn't see that flag.
#
# This .npmrc makes the project-wide default `--legacy-peer-deps`,
# which both `npm install` and `npm ci` honor. CI now installs the
# same way I do locally, and the deploy unblocks.
#
# Trade: peer-dep mismatches go undetected at install time. Acceptable
# for a small private project with one team; if we ever ship as a
# library we'd want to either pin firebase v12 or remove the
# @capacitor-firebase/messaging plugin (now dead code on native since
# the FCM v1 disable in bc89364).
legacy-peer-deps=true
